[Event "Baker Bridge - Overcalls and TakeOut Doubles"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "1"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "W:A76.Q85.A932.T94 K983.76.KQ5.AJ76 T54.JT92.JT86.53 QJ2.AK43.74.KQ82"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1D pass pass X pass 2D pass 2H pass 2S pass 3C pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 1, chOption: N, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 0, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "d69fed6f7545b33c33a9de694bb82ba864fecfffa1a3b690d4083af235e5f79d"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 13 points but has no bid over 1\D. 
SOUTH can make a Takeout Double, so he does.

NORTH now cue-bids \D to show opening hand strength.

SOUTH shows his \H suit, NORTH doesn't like it. 
NORTH shows her \S suit, SOUTH doesn't like it. 
SOUTH shows his \C suit, NORTH likes it fine, but decides 3NT will be easier than 5\C.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "E:K82.KJT2.KQ9.Q83 AJT74.A73.A86.95 Q53.984.T32.AJ74 96.Q65.J754.KT62"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "1S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: E, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 1, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "01d11fd554f795a38f23f5019ff255d344b8710d42c59e43caf6f351f383c1e4"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH would have had a great opening 1\S bid. But when EAST opened 1\S 
in front of him he was hornswaggled. He couldn't bid any other suit, he couldn't bid 1NT 
and he sure couldn't bid \Ss. So he must pass.

And so does everybody else pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:6.AQT8.JT75.QT84 KQJ9753.74.Q3.62 T4.K963.A42.AKJ9 A82.J52.K986.753"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1C 3S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "5384859383065be68f624904d24f933047682ed39f68fd6ed7fe85e471e9a676"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{If East had passed, SOUTH would have opened with a preemptive 3\S.

She should make the same bid with the same hand AFTER the opponents open. And she makes it 
for the same reason, to describe her hand and to take away bidding space from the opponents.

NORTH treats it just like a Preemptive 3-bid, even though it is now called a Weak Jump Overcall. 
In this case, NORTH passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "S:963.AK7.942.AT75 AJT85.63.AJT85.3 Q4.T982.KQ7.KQJ2 K72.QJ54.63.9864"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "1S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1C 1S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "a03ff51f8e96ef047cbc3c143c9abc2d55f970786f3d41d966d610db90b7881b"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/overcalls"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has 12 points, but with two 5-card suits worthy of an overcall. There isn't really a 
right and wrong here, but it usually works out best to overcall in the higher-ranking suit. That 
leaves open the possibility of bidding the second suit later.

In this Deal, after WEST overcalls 1\S, that later possibility never happens because 
everybody should pass.}

